    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Complexs comprising a forum and adjacent basilica, forming the civic administrative center of a Roman community. A typical plan included a rectangular open marketplace surrounded on three sides by rooms, and basilican great hall and with a rear range of rooms.</Note_Text>
